Common.Strapline.Common.Text: TWO (2) MAJOR PRIME ASSETS ALONG DANDENONG'S RETAIL GOLDEN MILE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
+Landlord favoured triple net lease to Care Park, an end-to-end parking service provider, with over 25 years in operation and more than 450 owned and managed car parks across five countries.

+Providing net annual income of $220,000* through a 7 year lease with fixed 2%* annual rental increases.

+Featuring 168 car parking bays in a multi deck configuration within the ‘Hub Arcade’, currently operating 7 days a week as an auto pay boom gate operation.

+Located in Dandenong’s main retail, dining and commercial catchment, with easy access to public transport, major roads and freeway networks.

+Dandenong is the major commercial retail and industrial centre for Melbourne’s south-eastern suburbs.

+Often referred to as Melbourne’s second CBD, major employers include the Australian Taxation Office and the Dandenong and District Hospital, with the area also featuring a number of retirement villages and nursing homes, the Dandenong Market and Dandenong Plaza Shopping Centre.

+Defensive investment asset class, with low operating expenses, increasing demand from commuters and diminishing competition in the car park sector.
